title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\AuditLogConfig
name: AuditLogConfig
description:
Provides the configuration for logging a type of permissions. Example: { "audit_log_configs": [ { "log_type": "DATA_READ", "exempted_members": [ "user:jose@example.com" ] }, { "log_type": "DATA_WRITE" } ] } This enables 'DATA_READ' and 'DATA_WRITE' logging, while exempting jose@example.com from DATA_READ logging.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.AuditLogConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.exempted_members
params.description: Specifies the identities that do not cause logging for this type of permission. Follows the same format of [Binding.members][].

params.name: data.log_type
params.description: The log type that this config enables.
